==English==
===Etymology===
From latinized Greek "''electrinus''" "made of amber", from ancient Greek  [[ήλεκτρον]] (''elektron'') "amber", from [[ηλέκτωρ]] (''elektor'') "shiny, bright", from [[ήλιος]](''elios'') "sun".
=== Adjective ===
'''electric'''
# Of, relating to, produced by, operated with, or utilising [[electricity]]; [[electrical]]
# of, or relating to an [[electronic]] version of a [[musical instrument]] that has an [[acoustic]] equivalent
# [[emotionally]] [[thrilling]]; [[electrifying]]
=== Noun ===
'''electric'''
# an electric [[car]]
